TLDR: just don't go there, there are better banks in Paris.  Every interaction with them is painful. They always find ways to surprise me with their incompetence. Pending issue for 3 months now (due to their error, duh): watch them reply to this review before actually coming back to me by email or phone about my issue :) btw: you should read the 5* reviews here - they all have the same format (they are fake). Their incompetence is such that they can't even make fake reviews look legit. Some relatives and myself had to close our accounts after more than 10 years of service going downhill.

I was particularly satisfied with the immediate and excellent service of Mr. Rayan Djadda. The atmosphere was always pleasant and friendly, he answered all of my questions in detail and always with a smile. My request was fulfilled very quickly and without any hassle! Thank you very much again.

I had an appointment at Societe Generale to change my card and assurance. Mrs. Marie Seck helped me with all the documents. She was very helpful and friendly. I also appreciated that she tried to speak English as well since I didn‚Äôt understand everything in French.

This is the worst bank branch I have ever come across in any country; had it been possible I would have given zero stars. I have never gone in to them with a problem that they have fixed - I usually have more problems after contacting them than I did before. They never answer their phone and they couldn't even block a lost/stolen check book - an emergency service... I also think multiple of the employees at this branch are paying for reviews: when was the last time anyone you know named their bank counsellor in an honest review? Pretty rare, no? Yet here most positive reviews have a named counsellor in them... DO NOT OPEN AN ACCOUNT HERE!!!

Horrible service. I came with 4 other students to open a bank account and we all waited 2 hours (estimated wait time was 30 minutes) to open an account, which is ridiculous. They said they would provide service in English (which I would have appreciated since my French is only level B2), but they never spoke to me in anything but French. They had multiple issues with my email and phone number, not getting it right and having to confirm the information 2 hours after I even entered the bank. And for some reason, it takes 10 minutes just to change my phone number. And after you open an account, it still won't be valid until 48 hours later. Horrible bank, do not go here. Literally find any other bank.
